The Budget and Appropriations committee has approved Sh1.9 trillion spending for ministries, state departments, and agencies. Chairman Kimani Ichung’wa announced this on Thursday when he tabled the committee’s report for debate. The report’s adoption will pave the way for Treasury Cabinet Secretary Ukur Yatani to read the Budget for financial year 2020-21 next Thursday. Parliament has been allocated Sh37.7 billion; Judiciary Sh18.05 billion; while the Executive has the lion share at Sh1.83 trillion. The Presidency’s budget has increased to Sh36.6 billion factoring the inclusion of the Nairobi Metropolitan Services. The Ichung’wa-led committee has further approved Sh131 billion for the Interior ministry of which Sh95 billion will go to policing services.